# -*- encoding: utf-8 -*-
# Arc: MagePath | Scene: FallOfLethram2
# Source: C:\Program Files (x86)\Steam\steamapps\common\The Survival of Sarah Rose\game\script.rpy

translate ru strings:

    old "As Sarah walked back home, she stumbled through the early streets of Lethram."
    new "Пока Сара шла домой, она бродила по утренним улицам Летрама."

    old "The sun had only just begun to crawl across the horizon, covering the world in gold."
    new "The sun had only just begun to crawl across the horizon, covering the world in gold."

    old "As she reached the top of the hill, close to her home, she turned and watched out across Lethram."
    new "As she reached the top of the hill, close to her home, she turned and watched out across Lethram."

    old "As the the sun rose further, the golden light receded."
    new "Когда солнце поднялось выше, золотой свет отступил."

    old "A blue sky, save for a few clouds, crowned the start of a new day in Lethram."
    new "Голубое небо, если не считать нескольких облаков, венчало начало нового дня в Летраме."

    old "And she remained transfixed on the sight."
    new "И она застыла, заворожённая этим зрелищем."

    old "As if she was hoping to capture something, imprint it to her mind."
    new "Словно надеялась запечатлеть что-то, отпечатать это в своей памяти."

    old "Sarah felt a surge of emotions she could not quite place, nor understand the origin of."
    new "Сара почувствовала всплеск эмоций, которым не могла найти объяснения, ни понять их источник."

    old "Building ever deeper in her chest."
    new "Они росли всё глубже в её груди."

    old "The many emotions grew into a torrent, and one by one they faded away."
    new "Множество эмоций превратились в бурный поток, и одна за другой они утихли."

    old "Until only one remained."
    new "Until only one remained."

    old "Dread."
    new "Dread."

    old "Sarah watched the city of Lethram, play out as it always had."
    new "Sarah watched the city of Lethram, play out as it always had."

    old "The day, if anything, more peaceful than most. The weather, clear."
    new "The day, if anything, more peaceful than most. The weather, clear."

    old "The many ships in the harbor that looked so small from this distance."
    new "The many ships in the harbor that looked so small from this distance."

    old "Why then, did she want to scream?"
    new "Why then, did she want to scream?"

    old "Yell for them to run."
    new "Yell for them to run."

    old "Sarah looked down and felt her hands tremble."
    new "Sarah looked down and felt her hands tremble."

    old "And her heart froze."
    new "And her heart froze."

    old "By sheer circumstance of fate, or a nervousness of character, Sarah looked up into the sky."
    new "By sheer circumstance of fate, or a nervousness of character, Sarah looked up into the sky."

    old "Her eyes fixed on the impossibility that floated in the air."
    new "Her eyes fixed on the impossibility that floated in the air."

    old "A black scar, a void, an absence."
    new "A black scar, a void, an absence."

    old "And within it, a writhing horde."
    new "And within it, a writhing horde."

    old "Sarah felt her body react with a primal fear."
    new "Sarah felt her body react with a primal fear."

    old "Her eyes went wide as he stared into the horror."
    new "Her eyes went wide as he stared into the horror."

    old "The obsidian impossibility that lingered in the sky, violating reality, wobbled for a brief moment."
    new "The obsidian impossibility that lingered in the sky, violating reality, wobbled for a brief moment."

    old "Sarah felt the horrifying grip on her heart as she watched the violent expulsion of the void scar."
    new "Sarah felt the horrifying grip on her heart as she watched the violent expulsion of the void scar."

    old "The miniscule anomaly that she had spotted, had expanded into the size of nearly a fifth of the city, seemingly in an instant."
    new "The miniscule anomaly that she had spotted, had expanded into the size of nearly a fifth of the city, seemingly in an instant."

    old "The force of it was like an explosion, wiping out the entire block of houses, entire streets."
    new "The force of it was like an explosion, wiping out the entire block of houses, entire streets."

    old "Broken fragments of rock and wood shot out across the city, landing with a brutal crash."
    new "Broken fragments of rock and wood shot out across the city, landing with a brutal crash."

    old "Around her, Sarah saw stunned faces, turning towards the horror."
    new "Around her, Sarah saw stunned faces, turning towards the horror."

    old "From a distance, she heard the torrent of screams."
    new "From a distance, she heard the torrent of screams."

    old "All of the city seemed to scream at once."
    new "All of the city seemed to scream at once."

    old "The types of screams that people only uttered when they were certain of death."
    new "The types of screams that people only uttered when they were certain of death."

    old "Her whole body shook as she tried to process what was happening."
    new "Her whole body shook as she tried to process what was happening."

    old "All of it seemed impossible, were it not her own eyes that were showing her it was all real."
    new "All of it seemed impossible, were it not her own eyes that were showing her it was all real."

    old "Then, some part of her regained control of herself."
    new "Then, some part of her regained control of herself."

    old "She needed to act."
    new "She needed to act."

    old "Everyone!"
    new "Everyone!"

    old "Sarah yelled out, snapping the other people near her from their stunned stupor."
    new "Sarah yelled out, snapping the other people near her from their stunned stupor."

    old "Head to the docks, now!"
    new "Head to the docks, now!"

    old "The void incursion had struck the northern part of the city, leaving the docks as the only safe part of Lethram."
    new "The void incursion had struck the northern part of the city, leaving the docks as the only safe part of Lethram."

    old "It would also be the best way to bring thousands of people to safety."
    new "It would also be the best way to bring thousands of people to safety."

    old "Already, Sarah saw the crawling and shifting shadows emerge out from the tear in reality."
    new "Already, Sarah saw the crawling and shifting shadows emerge out from the tear in reality."

    old "Memories of Bagrad came to her."
    new "Memories of Bagrad came to her."

    old "The Beast."
    new "The Beast."

    old "Get to safety!!!"
    new "Get to safety!!!"

    old "Sarah yelled out as she began to run."
    new "Sarah yelled out as she began to run."

    old "All around her, she saw people begin to turn and run."
    new "All around her, she saw people begin to turn and run."

    old "The mob of people began to surge as one, rushing in the direction of the docks."
    new "The mob of people began to surge as one, rushing in the direction of the docks."

    old "Sarah alone ran in the opposite direction. Towards the void."
    new "Sarah alone ran in the opposite direction. Towards the void."

    old "Her feets pounded against the hard cobblestone as she rushed up the hill."
    new "Her feets pounded against the hard cobblestone as she rushed up the hill."

    old "Around her, the torrent of people fleeing, storming past her as she made her way further up the hill."
    new "Around her, the torrent of people fleeing, storming past her as she made her way further up the hill."

    old "A man stumbled, his shoulder bashing into her."
    new "A man stumbled, his shoulder bashing into her."

    old "A woman grabbed at her arm for a moment, before she too was knocked over."
    new "A woman grabbed at her arm for a moment, before she too was knocked over."

    old "The people rushed down the road like a wave."
    new "The people rushed down the road like a wave."

    old "Sarah dodged and weaved between the bodies. It took everything in her power not to be swept aside by the mob."
    new "Sarah dodged and weaved between the bodies. It took everything in her power not to be swept aside by the mob."

    old "And in the midsts of it all, the growing screams."
    new "And in the midsts of it all, the growing screams."

    old "Panicked at first, but now the screams of people that realize death was only a mistake away."
    new "Panicked at first, but now the screams of people that realize death was only a mistake away."

    old "The sound pounded against her ears, as the bodies slammed into her."
    new "The sound pounded against her ears, as the bodies slammed into her."

    old "Just as she neared the top of the hill, another wave of people came running down."
    new "Just as she neared the top of the hill, another wave of people came running down."

    old "The first wave of people fleeing had been those in the streets."
    new "The first wave of people fleeing had been those in the streets."

    old "But this group had been the people nearer to the market. The busiest section of the city."
    new "But this group had been the people nearer to the market. The busiest section of the city."

    old "Sarah lunged aside, jumping into an alley only just in time."
    new "Sarah lunged aside, jumping into an alley only just in time."

    old "The hard stone cut into her arms, scraping up her clothes, blood forming."
    new "The hard stone cut into her arms, scraping up her clothes, blood forming."

    old "Each of her senses, racked and ruined by the surging and rushing tides of people."
    new "Each of her senses, racked and ruined by the surging and rushing tides of people."

    old "Mad people that fled like animals from a fire."
    new "Mad people that fled like animals from a fire."

    old "Fleeing something they understood only on a primal level."
    new "Fleeing something they understood only on a primal level."

    old "Sarah looked out from the alley as a woman slipped and fell."
    new "Sarah looked out from the alley as a woman slipped and fell."

    old "A single mistake."
    new "A single mistake."

    old "Sarah watched as the stomping and crushing feet of the mob swiftly ended the woman's life."
    new "Sarah watched as the stomping and crushing feet of the mob swiftly ended the woman's life."

    old "Through the swarming feet, Sarah could see the shapes of more bodies."
    new "Through the swarming feet, Sarah could see the shapes of more bodies."

    old "A deep panic had overtaken the people of Lethram."
    new "A deep panic had overtaken the people of Lethram."

    old "With trembling hands, Sarah pulled herself up, pushing against the wall of the alley."
    new "With trembling hands, Sarah pulled herself up, pushing against the wall of the alley."

    old "Looking out at the mob, she knew there was no way to make her way through."
    new "Looking out at the mob, she knew there was no way to make her way through."

    old "She'd had to go over."
    new "She'd had to go over."

    old "Slowly, she found the calm balance she needed, and silenced the senses. Drove out the outer world."
    new "Slowly, she found the calm balance she needed, and silenced the senses. Drove out the outer world."

    old "Until only the inner remained."
    new "Until only the inner remained."

    old "She channelled the magical energy in her legs and leapt out onto the roof."
    new "She channelled the magical energy in her legs and leapt out onto the roof."

    old "All at once, her body rushed up, leaving the city streets far behind her."
    new "All at once, her body rushed up, leaving the city streets far behind her."

    old "With a heavy crack, she landed on top of one of the many houses of Lethram."
    new "With a heavy crack, she landed on top of one of the many houses of Lethram."

    old "Some of the rooftiles cracked and slipped, falling down onto the streets below."
    new "Some of the rooftiles cracked and slipped, falling down onto the streets below."

    old "From this vantage point, Sarah looked out across the city."
    new "From this vantage point, Sarah looked out across the city."

    old "The panic had struck everywhere."
    new "The panic had struck everywhere."

    old "Every street in Lethram was filled with panicked mobs, rushing in every direction."
    new "Every street in Lethram was filled with panicked mobs, rushing in every direction."

    old "But most were heading towards the docks. The only real chance anyone had."
    new "But most were heading towards the docks. The only real chance anyone had."

    old "Turning her head, Sarah looked out across the city, towards the void incursion."
    new "Turning her head, Sarah looked out across the city, towards the void incursion."

    old "There, the black violation of natural space, still loomed."
    new "There, the black violation of natural space, still loomed."

    old "Peering into it, even from this distance, she could see the writhing masses of black shapeless tendrils."
    new "Peering into it, even from this distance, she could see the writhing masses of black shapeless tendrils."

    old "A horde of impossible creatures that had never been meant for this world."
    new "A horde of impossible creatures that had never been meant for this world."

    old "They poured out from the gate like a river of ink."
    new "They poured out from the gate like a river of ink."

    old "And high above, Sarah could hear the countless screams of the people of Lethram, carried on the wind."
    new "And high above, Sarah could hear the countless screams of the people of Lethram, carried on the wind."

    old "She clutched the roof for balance as the world spun about her."
    new "She clutched the roof for balance as the world spun about her."

    old "What could she even hope to do against this?"
    new "What could she even hope to do against this?"

    old "In a brief instance, the whole of the world had seemingly been turned over."
    new "In a brief instance, the whole of the world had seemingly been turned over."

    old "Looking down from the roof, Sarah saw the remains of the city market."
    new "Looking down from the roof, Sarah saw the remains of the city market."

    old "Carts overturned, produce scattered about, smashed stalls."
    new "Carts overturned, produce scattered about, smashed stalls."

    old "People, still running, screaming, stumbling as they madly tried to stay ahead of what was coming."
    new "People, still running, screaming, stumbling as they madly tried to stay ahead of what was coming."

    old "On the far end of the market, Sarah saw the first of the void beasts, rushing into the square."
    new "On the far end of the market, Sarah saw the first of the void beasts, rushing into the square."

    old "It moved, not as an animale might, but like flowing water."
    new "It moved, not as an animale might, but like flowing water."

    old "One tendril twisted and reached out, pulling the writhing mass forward."
    new "One tendril twisted and reached out, pulling the writhing mass forward."

    old "Then, its body like liquid ink, twisted and warped forward."
    new "Then, its body like liquid ink, twisted and warped forward."

    old "If it had any certain shape, it was soley in the white, pale mask that moved about the body."
    new "If it had any certain shape, it was soley in the white, pale mask that moved about the body."

    old "The only constant in an otherwise chaos."
    new "The only constant in an otherwise chaos."

    old "Every part of her wanted to run and flee."
    new "Every part of her wanted to run and flee."

    old "But just as she might have given into the instinct, Sarah saw a young girl."
    new "But just as she might have given into the instinct, Sarah saw a young girl."

    old "Too slow to run, she had taken to hiding under a broken stall."
    new "Too slow to run, she had taken to hiding under a broken stall."

    old "Hiding poorly."
    new "Hiding poorly."

    old "The writhing beasts lumbered forward."
    new "The writhing beasts lumbered forward."

    old "As it moved, it's tendril lashed out at the few people that had failed to make their escape."
    new "As it moved, it's tendril lashed out at the few people that had failed to make their escape."

    old "Men. Women. The creature did not seem to even hestitate."
    new "Men. Women. The creature did not seem to even hestitate."

    old "It lashed out with such force that the bodies of its victims exploded into mist and gore."
    new "It lashed out with such force that the bodies of its victims exploded into mist and gore."

    old "Life after life, snuffed out with as little as thought to care."
    new "Life after life, snuffed out with as little as thought to care."

    old "Sarah saw the girl, clutching the broken stall, pulling the canvas closer, hoping it might keep her safe."
    new "Sarah saw the girl, clutching the broken stall, pulling the canvas closer, hoping it might keep her safe."

    old "Then she leapt from the rooftop."
    new "Then she leapt from the rooftop."

    old "Magical energy surged, its binding slowing her descent as she landed in the center of the market."
    new "Magical energy surged, its binding slowing her descent as she landed in the center of the market."

    old "Instantly, the void creature turned towards her."
    new "Instantly, the void creature turned towards her."

    old "It's pale mask, peering in her direction."
    new "It's pale mask, peering in her direction."

    old "With great force, its shadowy tendrils dug into the earth, and the hulking mass began to drag itself towards her."
    new "With great force, its shadowy tendrils dug into the earth, and the hulking mass began to drag itself towards her."

    old "Sarah turned towards the girl."
    new "Sarah turned towards the girl."

    old "She motioned for her to stay, and worldlessly, saw that the girl understood."
    new "She motioned for her to stay, and worldlessly, saw that the girl understood."

    old "Sarah turned back, facing the advancing abomination."
    new "Sarah turned back, facing the advancing abomination."

    old "Raising up her hands, she summoned the blue flame that now came easy to her."
    new "Raising up her hands, she summoned the blue flame that now came easy to her."

    old "Around her hands, she saw the air warping from the surging heat."
    new "Around her hands, she saw the air warping from the surging heat."

    old "Everything Xan had ever taught her was that individual lives didn't matter. That a mage had to look at the bigger picture."
    new "Everything Xan had ever taught her was that individual lives didn't matter. That a mage had to look at the bigger picture."

    old "But that couldn't be true, Sarah thought as the beast advanced on her."
    new "But that couldn't be true, Sarah thought as the beast advanced on her."

    old "She heard the soft cries of the girl, doing her best to stay quiet."
    new "She heard the soft cries of the girl, doing her best to stay quiet."

    old "A force pulled on her that ran deeper than any cold logic that Xan had tried to instil in her."
    new "A force pulled on her that ran deeper than any cold logic that Xan had tried to instil in her."

    old "And she rushed forward."
    new "And she rushed forward."

    old "Thrusting her arms forward, the pale flame surged towards the beast."
    new "Thrusting her arms forward, the pale flame surged towards the beast."

    old "And as the magical fire struck its inky body, the creature screamed."
    new "And as the magical fire struck its inky body, the creature screamed."

    old "A high pitched, furious scream, like an animal snared in a trap."
    new "A high pitched, furious scream, like an animal snared in a trap."

    old "The beast flinched, its inky shifting mass flailing about as it tried to recover its balance."
    new "The beast flinched, its inky shifting mass flailing about as it tried to recover its balance."

    old "It's shadowy tendrils drilled into the earth, tethering itself in place."
    new "It's shadowy tendrils drilled into the earth, tethering itself in place."

    old "Sarah watched as its body warped, producing a maw with gaping teeth from where before there had been nothing."
    new "Sarah watched as its body warped, producing a maw with gaping teeth from where before there had been nothing."

    old "A snapping sound rang close to her hear as the beast lunged forward."
    new "A snapping sound rang close to her hear as the beast lunged forward."

    old "She rolled back, dodging the beasts ravenous maw."
    new "She rolled back, dodging the beasts ravenous maw."

    old "Again, again, she heard the snapping sound just as it missed her."
    new "Again, again, she heard the snapping sound just as it missed her."

    old "Sarah raised up her arms, plunging the pale flame directly into the beasts flesh, if it even had any."
    new "Sarah raised up her arms, plunging the pale flame directly into the beasts flesh, if it even had any."

    old "Again it screamed with animalistic fury as it stumbled about."
    new "Again it screamed with animalistic fury as it stumbled about."

    old "Sarah pressed her advantage, casting more of the flame into the beasts form."
    new "Sarah pressed her advantage, casting more of the flame into the beasts form."

    old "With each ball of fire that struck the beast, it scrambled further back."
    new "With each ball of fire that struck the beast, it scrambled further back."

    old "Screaming, crawling, it seemed desperate to escape."
    new "Screaming, crawling, it seemed desperate to escape."

    old "But Sarah did not yield her advantage."
    new "But Sarah did not yield her advantage."

    old "With practiced skill, she pressed on, and with each step, drove the best further back."
    new "With practiced skill, she pressed on, and with each step, drove the best further back."

    old "The first bolts of fire had merely whipped the beast, but by now the pale flame crawled across its skin."
    new "The first bolts of fire had merely whipped the beast, but by now the pale flame crawled across its skin."

    old "Translucent, blue light, shimmered within its internal black form, giving depth to void."
    new "Translucent, blue light, shimmered within its internal black form, giving depth to void."

    old "And slowly, her fire chipped away at the beast."
    new "And slowly, her fire chipped away at the beast."

    old "It collapsed from the pain, no longer able to yield, though it still screamed with infernal panic."
    new "It collapsed from the pain, no longer able to yield, though it still screamed with infernal panic."

    old "Sarah rained down all the fire she could on the beasts remains."
    new "Sarah rained down all the fire she could on the beasts remains."

    old "Like water to flame, the creature's body evaporated, becoming finally silent."
    new "Like water to flame, the creature's body evaporated, becoming finally silent."

    old "For a moment, Sarah stared at her victory."
    new "For a moment, Sarah stared at her victory."

    old "She had done it. Killed one of the blasted things."
    new "She had done it. Killed one of the blasted things."

    old "This was one was signficantly smaller than the one from Bagrad, but it confirmed to her that they could die."
    new "This was one was signficantly smaller than the one from Bagrad, but it confirmed to her that they could die."

    old "Just as she felt a moment of calm, Sarah heard the young girl screaming."
    new "Just as she felt a moment of calm, Sarah heard the young girl screaming."

    old "Sarah turned towards her."
    new "Sarah turned towards her."

    old "Frightend, the young girl was pointing towards the far end of the market."
    new "Frightend, the young girl was pointing towards the far end of the market."

    old "As Sarah looked in that direction, she saw."
    new "As Sarah looked in that direction, she saw."

    old "A horde of the beasts, stumbling madly into the market square."
    new "A horde of the beasts, stumbling madly into the market square."

    old "Wasting not a moment, Sarah dashed across the market towards the young girl."
    new "Wasting not a moment, Sarah dashed across the market towards the young girl."

    old "The girl reached out her hand and Sarah seized it."
    new "The girl reached out her hand and Sarah seized it."

    old "Pulling the girl up to her chest, she wrapped her arms around her waist."
    new "Pulling the girl up to her chest, she wrapped her arms around her waist."

    old "Fear and panic was painted all across the girl's face."
    new "Fear and panic was painted all across the girl's face."

    old "Hold onto me, okay?"
    new "Hold onto me, okay?"

    old "The young girl softly nodded."
    new "The young girl softly nodded."

    old "Just keep looking at me. Don't look at them."
    new "Just keep looking at me. Don't look at them."

    old "Sarah looked towards the rooftops."
    new "Sarah looked towards the rooftops."

    old "We're going to fly, so hold on."
    new "We're going to fly, so hold on."

    old "The magical energies rushed into her feet, and with impossible force, Sarah leapt across the sky."
    new "The magical energies rushed into her feet, and with impossible force, Sarah leapt across the sky."

    old "Rushing through the sky, Sarah felt the girl gripping onto her tighter."
    new "Rushing through the sky, Sarah felt the girl gripping onto her tighter."

    old "And Sarah found herself doing the same, making sure the girl would not slip."
    new "And Sarah found herself doing the same, making sure the girl would not slip."

    old "Magical tethers gripped around them, slowing their fall as they landed on one of the nearby rooftops."
    new "Magical tethers gripped around them, slowing their fall as they landed on one of the nearby rooftops."

    old "Down below, Sarah saw the advancing horde, rampaging through the market place, destroying anything they could reach."
    new "Down below, Sarah saw the advancing horde, rampaging through the market place, destroying anything they could reach."

    old "Killing anyone they could."
    new "Killing anyone they could."

    old "Sarah was not blind to the world. In her travels with Xan she had learned and seen a lot."
    new "Sarah was not blind to the world. In her travels with Xan she had learned and seen a lot."

    old "Even the cruelties of men, victorious in war."
    new "Even the cruelties of men, victorious in war."

    old "But she had never seen destruction like this."
    new "But she had never seen destruction like this."

    old "Even cruel warlords sought to conquer for a purpose."
    new "Even cruel warlords sought to conquer for a purpose."

    old "But these beasts seemed to be moved by only destruction."
    new "But these beasts seemed to be moved by only destruction."

    old "Sarah looked at the girl."
    new "Sarah looked at the girl."

    old "Are you okay?"
    new "Are you okay?"

    old "Again, slowly, the girl nodded."
    new "Again, slowly, the girl nodded."

    old "Okay, keep hanging on, we need to get to safety."
    new "Okay, keep hanging on, we need to get to safety."

    old "Again, the energy surged through her legs."
    new "Again, the energy surged through her legs."

    old "With magical force, Sarah repeated the same feat, leaping from building to building."
    new "With magical force, Sarah repeated the same feat, leaping from building to building."

    old "Crossing through the city like this, she could cut right across the many twisting streets and alleys."
    new "Crossing through the city like this, she could cut right across the many twisting streets and alleys."

    old "Before long, she approached the docks."
    new "Before long, she approached the docks."

    old "Already, she could see countless thousands gathered up, rushing towards whatever boats they could find to escape."
    new "Already, she could see countless thousands gathered up, rushing towards whatever boats they could find to escape."

    old "Sarah leapt down towards the street level and released the girl."
    new "Sarah leapt down towards the street level and released the girl."

    old "She looked straight at the girl to make sure that she was listening."
    new "She looked straight at the girl to make sure that she was listening."

    old "You go down this street, straight down."
    new "You go down this street, straight down."

    old "You don't take any side turns, you just keep going directly down this street until you reach the docks, got it?"
    new "You don't take any side turns, you just keep going directly down this street until you reach the docks, got it?"

    old "The young girl nodded."
    new "The young girl nodded."

    old "When you get there, don't stop until you're on one of the boats."
    new "When you get there, don't stop until you're on one of the boats."

    old "Sarah saw more people running. Time was quickly running out."
    new "Sarah saw more people running. Time was quickly running out."

    old "Go on, go now! Run!"
    new "Go on, go now! Run!"

    old "The young girl gave a final nod, then turned and began to ran as quickly as her short legs could manage."
    new "The young girl gave a final nod, then turned and began to ran as quickly as her short legs could manage."

    old "Sarah prayed she'd make it."
    new "Sarah prayed she'd make it."

    old "Down below, in the docks, Sarah saw the endlessly growing wave of people fleeing."
    new "Down below, in the docks, Sarah saw the endlessly growing wave of people fleeing."

    old "The ships were filling up. Others still were coming into harbor, having realized what had happened."
    new "The ships were filling up. Others still were coming into harbor, having realized what had happened."

    old "It would take time for the ships to pull in and take on refugees."
    new "It would take time for the ships to pull in and take on refugees."

    old "Would they even have that time?"
    new "Would they even have that time?"

